cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives an information-theoretic lower bound on the minimum normalized delivery time (NDT) for arbitrary number of ENs and users, which falls under the scope of information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies the decentralized coded caching for a Fog Radio Access Network (F-RAN), which involves the design of a content placement and delivery scheme for wireless networks, falling under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a decentralized content placement and delivery scheme for a wireless network, which involves the design of a system with multiple nodes and control over the placement and delivery of content, falling under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a decentralized content placement and delivery scheme for a wireless network, which involves the design of a distributed system with multiple nodes and parallel processing of content, falling under the scope of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper studies the delivery of user demands for multimedia content in a wireless network, which involves the design of a multimedia system with multiple nodes and storage of multimedia content in caches, falling under the scope of multimedia.
